{"questionId":"11768","questionHtml":"<p>a formula for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"m\">\n  <mi>m</mi>\n</math></span> in terms of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"m = {e^{ - 1.4p + 10.24}}\\,\\,\\left( { = 28000{e^{ - 1.4p}}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>m</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>e</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>1.4</mn>\n        <mi>p</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mn>10.24</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n      <mn>28000</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>e</mi>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>1.4</mn>\n            <mi>p</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11768","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.13b.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"a formula for m in terms of p .","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.10—Scaling large numbers, log-log graphs"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}